905221821/http://legacy.icao.int/anb/aig/Taxonomy/R4CDLocationIndicatorsbystate.pdf |archivedate = 5 September 2012 |df = dmy-all }}\n* {{cite web |url = http://www.unece.org/fileadmin/DAM/cefact/locode/in.htm |title = UN Location Codes: India |work = [[UN/LOCODE]] 2009-1 |publisher = [[United Nations Economic Commission for Europe|UNECE]] |date = 23 September 2009}} - includes IATA codes\n* [http://www.gcmap.com/search?Q=country:IN Great Circle Mapper] - IATA and ICAO codes\n* [http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/india/airbase.htm List of Indian Air Force Stations] at GlobalSecurity.org\n* [http://www.pilotfriend.com/World%20airfield%20database/airfield%20codes/codes9/India2.htm PilotFriend - Indian Airstrips]\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140618154837/http://www.aai.aero/allAirports/airports.jsp List of airports mentioned by Airport Authority of India]\n\n{{Airports in India}}\n{{Transport in India}}\n{{Asia in topic|List of airports in}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List of Airports in India}}\n[[Category:Lists of airports in India| ]]\n[[Category:Airports in India| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of airports by country|India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{pp-pc}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{More footnotes|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n\n[[File:Airports and seaports map.png|thumb|300px|right|Airports and [[Ports in India|seaports]] in India]]\nThis '''lists of [[airport]]s in [[India]]''' includes existing and former, commercial airports, flying schools, military bases, etc. As per [[Airport Authority of India|AAI]] data from Nov 2016, following are being targeted for the scheduled commercial flight operations under [[UDAN|UDAN-RCS]], including the following:\n* 486 total airports, airstrips, flying schools and military bases are available in the country.\n* 123 airports with scheduled commercial flights including some with dual civilian and army use.\n* 34 international airports\n\n{{Maps/Airports in India}}\n\n==Contents==\n[[File:Busiest airports in India 2-01.png|thumb|300px|[[List of the busiest airports in India|Busiest Indian airports]] (2015-16)]]\n\nThis list contains the following information:\n#'''City served'''&nbsp;\u2013 The city generally associated with the airport. This is not always the actual location since some airports are located in smaller towns outside of the city they serve.\n#'''ICAO'''&nbsp;\u2013 The [[International Civil Aviation Organization airport code|location indicator]] assigned by the [[International Civil Aviation Organization]] (ICAO). ICAO indicator: VA&nbsp;\u2013 West Zone, VE&nbsp;\u2013 East Zone, VI&nbsp;\u2013 North Zone, VO&nbsp;\u2013 South Zone\n#'''IATA'''&nbsp;\u2013 The [[International Air Transport Association airport code|airport code]] assigned by the [[International Air Transport Association]] (IATA).\n#'''Category'''&nbsp;\u2013 Category of the airport as defined by [[Airports Authority of India]]<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.aai.aero/allAirports/airports.jsp |title=Airport Authority of India |publisher=Aai.aero |date=14 January 2015 |accessdate=17 April 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140618154837/http://www.aai.aero/allAirports/airports.jsp |archivedate=18 June 2014  }}</ref> as per the table below\n#'''Role'''&nbsp;\u2013 Role of the airport as given by the table below\n{|class=wikitable\n|+Category of Airport\n|-\n!style=\"width:100px;\"|Category\n!style=\"width:300px;\"|Description\n|-\n|style=\"background:#E0CEF2;\"|'''[[Customs Airport|Customs]]'''||Airports with Customs Checking and Clearance Facilities handling international flights but not elevated to International Airport status.\n|-\n|style=\"background:#CEF2E0;\"|'''Defence'''||Indian Armed Forces Handled Airport\n|-\n|style=\"background:#2F847C;\"|'''[[Domestic Airport|Domestic]]'''||Handles domestic flights\n|-\n| style=\"background:#0ff;\"|'''Future'''||Proposed or Under Construction\n|-\n|style=\"background:#9F8170;\"|'''[[International Airport|International]]'''||Handles International Flights\n|-\n|style=\"background:#CEE0F2;\"|'''Private'''||Private airport for specific purposes\n|}\n{|class=wikitable\n|+Role of Airport\n|-\n!Role\n!Description\n|-\n|[[Civil enclave]]||Civil Enclaves in a Military Airport. Handles Commercial Flights\n|-\n|style=\"background:#A0ACB8\"|Closed||No longer in operation for Commercial Flights\n|-\n|Commercial||Handles Commercial flights\n|-\n|[[Airbase]]||Military Airbase\n|-\n|[[Flight Training|Flying School]]||Airport used to train commercial and/or fighter pilots\n|}\n\n{|class=wikitable\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Commercial service||style=\"background:#ffe6b7;\"|Airport has commercial service\n|-\n| style=\"background:ivory;\"|Airport has no commercial service\n|}\n\n==List==\n\n===[[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]]===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:15%;\"|City Served\n!style=\"width:35%;\"|Airport Name\n!style=\"width:10%;\"|ICAO\n!style=\"width:10%;\"|IATA\n!style=\"width:10%;\"|Category\n!style=\"width:20%;\"|Role\n|-\n|[[Car Nicobar]]|| style=\"background:ivory;\"|[[Car Nicobar Air Force Base]]||align=center|VOCX||align=center|CBD||style=\"background:#CEF2E0;\"|Defence||Air Base\n|-\n|[[Campbell Bay (Great Nicobar)|Campbell Bay]]|| style=\"background:ivory;\"|[[INS Baaz]]||align=center|VO90<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.flyvictor.com/en-us/private-jet-airports/campbell-bay-airport-(vo94)/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=15 September 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915204133/https://www.flyvictor.com/en-us/private-jet-airports/campbell-bay-airport-(vo94)/ |archivedate=15 September 2017  }}</ref>||align=center|\u2014||style=\"background:#CEF2E0;\"|Defence||Air Base\n|-\n|[[Diglipur]]|| style=\"background:ivory;\"|[[INS Kohassa]]||align=center|VODX||align=center|IN-0053||style=\"background:#CEF2E0;\"|Defence||Air Base\n|-\n|